      <abstract id="aspace_dd301e6d080991b49cb34dcda24d3fb6">This collection contains more than 300 letters sent between William Halsey and Mary Price from 1916-1918. Halsey was an engineering professor at GW and Price was a personal secretary in Swarthmore, PA. Throughout the time the letters were written, Halsey and Price dated, got engaged, and married. The letters provide insight into love and courtship in the early 20th century and discuss events like the 1916 presidential election and World War I.</abstract>
      <physloc id="aspace_890e41243583f0da6008e74d10c2d255">Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time.  Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.</physloc>
